.TH WATCHGUARD 8 "2026-07-03" "watchguard 1.0.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
watchguard \- host health monitor for SSH, OOM, network, and DNS

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B watchguard daemon
[\-\-config /etc/watchguard/config.toml]

.B watchguard status
[\-\-config /etc/watchguard/config.toml]

.B watchguard doctor
[\-\-config /etc/watchguard/config.toml]

.B watchguard enable
.IR plugin

.B watchguard disable
.IR plugin
[\-\-remove]

.B watchguard config
.IR command

.SH DESCRIPTION
Watchguard is a plugin-based host health monitor designed for systemd Linux hosts.

It can monitor:
.IP \(bu 2
OOM events through journalctl kernel log following
.IP \(bu 2
sshd service state through systemd D-Bus
.IP \(bu 2
SSH target reachability through TCP probes
.IP \(bu 2
Outbound network reachability through TCP probes
.IP \(bu 2
DNS resolution through direct DNS queries

Watchguard supports boot grace and reboot cooldown failsafes to prevent reboot storms.

.SH PLUGINS
.TP
.B ssh
Monitors sshd service state and SSH TCP target reachability.

.TP
.B ssh-service
Enables or disables only the sshd service-state test.

.TP
.B ssh-targets
Enables or disables only the SSH target reachability test.

.TP
.B network
Monitors outbound TCP reachability.

.TP
.B dns
Monitors DNS resolution.

.TP
.B oom
Monitors OOM messages from journalctl.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B watchguard daemon
Runs the Watchguard daemon.

.TP
.B watchguard status
Prints enabled plugins and current status.

.TP
.B watchguard doctor
Runs environment, config, and live probe diagnostics.

.TP
.B watchguard enable ssh
Enables the SSH plugin.

.TP
.B watchguard disable ssh
Disables the SSH plugin while preserving its config.

.TP
.B watchguard disable ssh --remove
Removes the SSH plugin config table.

.TP
.B watchguard config init
Creates the default configuration file.

.TP
.B watchguard config validate
Validates the configuration.

.TP
.B watchguard config show
Prints the configuration.

.TP
.B watchguard config edit
Opens the configuration in $EDITOR, or vi if unset.

.SH CONFIGURATION
Default config path:

.I /etc/watchguard/config.toml

Durations use human-readable values:

.EX
500ms
2s
30s
1m
5m
30m
1h
.EE

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/watchguard
Watchguard binary.

.TP
.I /etc/watchguard/config.toml
Watchguard configuration.

.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/watchguard.service
systemd service unit.

.SH LOGS
View daemon logs with:

.EX
journalctl -u watchguard -f
.EE

.SH EXAMPLES
Enable SSH monitoring:

.EX
watchguard enable ssh
systemctl restart watchguard
.EE

Run diagnostics:

.EX
watchguard doctor
.EE

Enable network monitoring:

.EX
watchguard enable network
watchguard status
.EE

Enable OOM monitoring:

.EX
watchguard enable oom
systemctl restart watchguard
.EE

.SH AUTHOR
Watchguard project
